title: @OspreyWSOC Hosts NJIT and Lipscomb in Final Home Matches
text: 5' 8" Jr. JACKSONVILLE, Fla. â€“ The North Florida women's soccer team hosts their final two regular season home matches this weekend, facing conference foes NJIT Friday at 7:30 p.m. and Lipscomb Sunday at 1 p.m. The Ospreys (3-8-0, 1-1-0 A-Sun) currently sit in third place in the conference through their first two matches, including a 2-1 win over Stetson last weekend at Hodges Stadium. "We are looking forward to being at home for two important conference matches. It is a crucial weekend for us and we need to pick up some points," said coach . "When it comes to conference play every game is going to be competitive and tight, so we need to be at our best. We had a great week of training and are focused and ready." The Highlanders (2-9-0, 0-2-0 A-Sun) are coming off of a non-conference loss to Delaware State on Tuesday, after falling to Kennesaw State last Saturday. The Bisons (7-2-4, 2-0-0 A-Sun) are currently first in the conference following a win over USC Upstate last Saturday. They'll face Jacksonville on Friday before heading to Hodges Stadium.The Ospreys look to continue their strong defensive play this season. Goalkeeper
